COMMENT     PROVISIONAL REFSEQ: This record has not yet been subject to final
            NCBI review. The reference sequence is identical to J02146.
            [2],[1] sequence determined either by analysis of cloned cdna
            fragments [2] or by analysis of cdna synthesized with either
            poly-adenylated vrna template or vrna template and dodecamer primer
            [1]. assignment of coding region by consideration of open reading
            frames. [3] compares this na sequence with 11 other influenza
            strains and finds that the strains collected from 1933-1935 have
            deletions of 33 to 48bp in their seg 6 vrna 3' ends. the sequence
            figure for [3] was unclear at the extreme 3' end (bases 228-233).
            Complete source information:
            influenza A/Puerto Rico/8/34 [2]: rna & cdna to rna from human;
            [1],[3]: cdna to rna grown in chicken embryos, originally from
            human. [3] specifies A/Puerto Rico/8/34(mt. sinai).
            COMPLETENESS: full length.
